A BODY was found with two gunshot wounds to the head in Bethelsdorp on Saturday. The man, believed to be in his 20s, was dressed in blue jeans, a black hoodie and Adidas takkies. Police spokeswoman Colonel Priscilla Naidu said he still had a black rucksack on his back. At about 11pm on Saturday, a member of the public was walking on a footpath between Jacksonville and Booysen Park when they stumbled on the body, Naidu said. Police passing by were notified. At this stage, the motive is still unknown. Related Share on Facebook Share Share on Twitter Tweet Share on Google Plus Share